<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="view/macro:page/onecolumn"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>
<body>

  <metal:portlets fill-slot="portlets">
  </metal:portlets>

  <div metal:fill-slot="main">

    <div style="font-size: larger; background: #e0f0d0;
        padding: 0.3em; -moz-border-radius: 5px; -o-border-radius: 5px;
       -webkit-border-radius: 5px;">
      <strong>Requesting Ubuntu CDs</strong> is done at <a
      href="https://shipit.ubuntu.com/">shipit.ubuntu.com</a>
      <form style="display: inline; font-size: smaller"
            action="https://shipit.ubuntu.com/">
        <input type="submit" value="Oh, I want Ubuntu CDs" />
      </form>
    </div>

    <div style="font-size: normal; float: right; width: 15em; padding: 0.5em;
      background: #e0f0d0; margin: 0.5em; margin-left: 1em;
      border: 1px solid #ccc; -moz-border-radius: 5px;">
      <p style="margin: 0">Hi there! This is a message from the team
      that develops Launchpad (this is <a
      href="/~launchpad/+mugshots">what we look like</a> if you're
      curious).  We're working hard to make sure Launchpad is the best
      project hosting and registration site out there. We hope you enjoy
      it here.</p>

      <p style="margin-bottom: 0">PS: do <a href="/feedback">tell us</a>
      if you don't!</p>
    </div>

    <h2>A brand new project in Launchpad</h2>

    <p id="instructions" style="font-size: larger">
    Launchpad is a service for <strong>registering and hosting software
    projects</strong>. Service is provided free for open source/free software
    projects. But let us steal a minute of your time to point out a few
    important things before you proceed with the actual registration.
    </p>

    <ol style="font-size: larger">
      <li tal:condition="not: is_demo" id="staging-message">
      <strong>Want to test drive Launchpad?</strong>
      If you've never used Launchpad before, start off at <a
      href="https://staging.launchpad.net/"><strong>staging.launchpad.net</strong></a>,
      our code staging instance. You can use that server to create sample
      projects, file random bugs and even push throw-away branches, all
      without disturbing the community actively using Launchpad.</li>

      <li style="margin-top: 1em"><strong>Not sure what Launchpad is?</strong> It's
      many things (and sometimes a bit confusing); check out <a
      href="https://help.launchpad.net/FrontPage#user-guide">our user
      handbook</a> or, if you prefer, <a
      href="https://launchpad.net/+tour">take our guided tour</a>.</li>

      <li style="margin-top: 1em"><strong>Is the project already registered?</strong>
        Launchpad is both a hosting and a registration facility, and someone
        else may have already registered the project. <em>If you have not
        already searched for the project,</em>  then do so.
        <ul style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">
          <li>If you find a project you run,
          <a href="/launchpad/+addquestion">ask us</a> and we'll hand the
          project over to you.</li>
          <li>To set that project up for translation to your language, <a
          href="/rosetta/+addquestion">ask the Translations staff</a>.</li>
        </ul>
        <div>
          <strong>Projects in Launchpad:</strong>
          <form style="display: inline; font-size: smaller" action="/projects">
            <input type="text" name="text" />
            <input type="submit" value="Search" />
          </form>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li style="margin-top: 1em;">All set?
      Move on to <a href="/projects/+new"><strong>the registration form</strong></a>.
      Thanks for listening!</li>
    </ol>

  </div>

</body>
</html>
